<br>
As for wearing the other focus items, it doesn't really matter.  We know the mantle increases buff length, and it could decrease mana too.  However, we also know it only &quot;glows&quot; for only buffs.  So if it would only save mana for buffs.  This is why I chose to remove this one.  I wasn't wearing the neck, so if it does anything other than reduce reagent use, doesn't really matter since I wasn't wearing it.  So the 2 that I was wearing that do work with nukes, bracer and ring, are all that's left.  They <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> might</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> reduce mana, but since I was wearing them both for both tests it wouldn't matter.  Assuming they do reduce mana, depending on how the game calculates the reduction, it <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> could</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> cause the mana reduction figure to be inaccurate.  However, the ultimate result of the test is the same: Earring reduces mana on nukes and DoT's.<br>
<br>
As for running more trials.  Each trial takes about 20 minutes, I'd rather not spend 400 minutes doing it.  Two tests without the ear got exactly the same result and 3 with got exactly the same increase.  That's good enough for me, at least more than &quot;I think I was getting less agro.&quot;  Who knows though, maybe it does both <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>~~
